TY  - JOUR
AU  - Li, Dongmei
T1  - Financial Constraints, R&amp;D Investment, and Stock Returns
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhr043
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 24
IS  - 9
SP  - 2974
EP  - 3007
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Through the interaction between financial constraints and R&amp;D, I study two asset-pricing puzzles: mixed evidence on the financial constraints–return relation and the positive R&amp;D-return relation. Unlike capital investment, R&amp;D is more inflexible. A financially constrained R&amp;D-intensive firm is more likely to suspend/discontinue R&amp;D projects. Therefore, R&amp;D-intensive firms' risk increases with their financial constraints. Conversely, constrained firms' risk increases with their R&amp;D intensity. I find a robust empirical relation between financial constraints and stock returns, primarily among R&amp;D-intensive firms. Moreover, R&amp;D predicts returns only among financially constrained firms. This evidence suggests that financial constraints potentially drive the positive R&amp;D-return relation.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhr043
ER  - 



